    <text id="F8021T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Cameron tries to explain his campaign contributions.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Reply to<lb/><abbr expan="Alexander">A.</abbr> K. McClure
                    <hi rend="underline">Copy of reply</hi>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1860-08-01"><abbr expan="August">Aug.</abbr> 1, 1860</date>
                        <name type="place">
                            <unclear>Lochial</unclear>
                        </name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I have your letter of yesterday, and can only say that I have been
                    misrepresented, as usual, and that you have been imposed upon. Have you seen
                        <abbr expan="Colonel">Col.</abbr> Curtin? All I have consented to do, was in
                    accordance with his views, his knowledge &amp; his approbation.</p>
                <p>I was called on by local gentlemen of the "republican club" of the city and asked
                    and asked to object <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> in organizing for the campaign which I
                    consented to do only on condition that we should in no manner interfere with you
                    or your committee.</p>
                <p>So for have <unclear>infecting</unclear> to get <unclear>fired</unclear> from the
                        national<pb n="2"/>committee one of the <unclear>express</unclear>
                    conditions made by me was that we should express all offers of aid in money or
                    otherwise from persons outside the state.</p>
                <p>It is time I heard from all <unclear>sides</unclear> in <abbr
                        expan="Philadelphia">Phila</abbr> that you had given up the hope of
                    obtaining friends, and that you had said you would not again call your committee
                    together. I regret <unclear>foilcars</unclear> and was willing to forgo my own
                    comfort and neglect my own business to <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> you and others, in
                        <unclear>victory</unclear> harmony, and to bring about such a victory as we
                    may all be proud of.</p>
                <p>I can only account for your misapprehension of my <unclear>vices</unclear> by
                    believing that you have not <del rend="none" hand="h1"/>
                    <del rend="none" hand="h1"/>.</p>
                <pb n="3"/>
                <p>I have <unclear>planned</unclear> to be in <abbr expan="Philadelphia"
                    >Phila</abbr> Tuesday next, when I will be the gentlemen whom I proved to act
                    with and will also have a <unclear>frank</unclear> and cordial conversation with
                    you. I desire, however that you will write Mr. Curtin to be present, and will
                    not consent to be misunderstood by him.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Vly <del rend="none" hand="h1"/></salute>
                    <signed/>
                    <seg type="postscript">
                        <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Colonel">Col.</abbr>
                            <abbr expan="Alexander">A</abbr> K McClure</name>
                    </seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
